cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.GR, cs.CL

The paper proposes deep learning frameworks for the automatic identification of roads based on satellite data, which suggests that it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of deep learning methods also indicates that it could be classified under machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with the challenges of analyzing large-scale satellite data, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) or graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the proposed methods, which could involve natural language processing (cs.CL) for generating textual descriptions of the detected roads.
